What is an UNT?|
PG| ***** 146 ***** |


AT| In general an immediate overcall of 2NT after an Opponent opens either a major or a minor is an Unusual NT - UNT.|
PG| ***** 147 ***** |


AT| I like the definition in Bridge Guys web site |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgeguys.com/Conventions/UnusualNoTrump.html^*N|CP||AT|,  "The Unusual Notrump is a conventional defense method designed to show two suited hands in competitive situations with one bid."|
