AT| The bid always shows the two lower unbid suits - at least five cards in each suit. Therefore, after one of a majors opening it always shows the |cp|1|at|two minors|cp||at|. And after a minor opening it shows |cp|1|at| heart and the other minor|cp||at|. Let's look at the four possible UNT bids by partner sitting North:|
